<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1239204" src="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/download-6.jpg?resize=500%2C775&#038;ssl=1" alt="Customs intercepts illegal goods worth N997m in Sokoto in 2 months" width="500" height="775" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/download-6.jpg?resize=661%2C1024&amp;ssl=1 661w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/download-6.jpg?resize=194%2C300&amp;ssl=1 194w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/download-6.jpg?resize=768%2C1190&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/download-6.jpg?resize=37%2C58&amp;ssl=1 37w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/download-6.jpg?resize=125%2C194&amp;ssl=1 125w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/download-6.jpg?resize=84%2C130&amp;ssl=1 84w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/download-6.jpg?resize=560%2C868&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/download-6.jpg?w=1500&amp;ssl=1 1500w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/download-6.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The Sokoto/Zamfara Command of Nigerian Customs Service (NCS) has intercepted 640 cartons of sexual enhancing drugs, an AK47 Gun and other illegally smuggled items worth N997 million from October and November. Mr. Magaji Mailafiya, the Command’s Public Relations Officer (PRO) made the disclosure in a statement he available to the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) in Sokoto on Tuesday. Mailafiya said no fewer 29 seizures were made within the periods under review. He said the smuggled goods had the duty paid value of N915 million, adding that they were arrested along Ilella-Kware road on Nov. 3. He said on Nov. 25, the personnel of the command also arrested three Toyota, Carina II vehicles loaded with 132 Jerry Cans of 25kg Vegetable oil, 85 cartons of Tiger Head Batteries and 86 sacks of 25kg size Monosodium Glutamate at Achida/Goronyo road. Mailafiya added that command’s men on patrol on Nov. 20, also seized seven sacks containing 800 pieces of cutlass stressing that efforts were part of the fight against smuggling in the country. The customs` spokesman reiterated Sokoto/Zamfara Area Command’s commitment, headed by Comptroller Umar Gimba, to ensure smuggle free economy in the nation through intelligence gathering and constant patrols. He appealed to the general public to embrace legitimate trade and avoid smuggling, stressing that the area command would not relent in its concerted effort at ensuring that smuggling activities are brought to the barest minimum. The PRO enjoined Nigerians to cooperate with the operatives of the area command, especially in the border communities, to allow for the socio-economic growth of the country. According to him, this will help to provide the needed employment for the people, stressing that smuggling cripples the nation’s economy. vanguard The Kebbi, Sokoto and Zamfara Zonal Command of the Nigerian Customs Service, NCS, last year, collected a total of N1.8 billion revenue, even as it impounded contraband goods worth N454.8 million during the same period. January 23, 2019 In "Custom Watch" The Nigerian Customs Service (NCS) Command in Sokoto, Kebbi and Zamfara says it has generated N829.5 million between May and October. November 1, 2017 In "News" The Sokoto Area Command of the Nigeria Customs Service (NCS) has intercepted two elephant tusks weighing 65 kilogrammes and valued at more than N14 million. September 27, 2017 In "News"